Ian Aelfstan Mallory asks if anyone else does bar brawls.
 
Barony Rivenstar has been doing them at Feast of Fools for a
number of years, I'm told.  I witnessed one--the rules seemed
to be exactly as you say.  Master Moonwulf, Baron Rivenstar
was deeply involved in the organization--he seemed to be both
barkeep and referee.  Tankards and the like were the weapons,
swords and shields were checked at the door, but it seems to me
there was some procedure whereby you could exit, pick them up
and fight.
 
As a spectator, I laughed myself silly.
 
This spectacle was complemented in the evening by "Not the Court
of Not Their Majesties Elen and Eliahu" (everyone put on their
groucho marx glasses) which made Palymar a "Court Duke" (complete
with tinfoil crown).
