was the heir of Louis IX and the cousin of the Eds. (HIII married
LIX's sister and LIX did the same for HIII.)  Philip was a bit of
weinie, if memory serves me correct.  He got his butt kicked in
a campaign against some Papal enemy (Hohenstaffen?) and spent the
rest of his reign looking for a war to win so he could 'redeem French
arms.' (They'd gone undefeated since Philip A.)  I think he was
the King who kidnapped the Pope and started the Babylonian captivity.

