In a recent missive, Ariel of Caer Myrddin described the problem of being
deluged by requests to "get So-And-So a Silver Crescent" as soon as she was
given the award.

My lady, I have been a Silver Crescent since last July (so it's still fairly
new to me as well), but I have not experienced the problems you've described.
Of course, we have several members of the order down here; if you're one of
a very few in your area, I can see how it would happen.

There is a very simple answer to these people who plague you.  Tell them to 
write their nominee in to the Crown, and you'll examine the situation when
the person shows up on the poll.  It doesn't take much to get someone on the
poll; anyone can write a recommendation.  (Randal and Katherine included on
the poll everyone who was written in.  It looks like Morguhn and Rowan are
doing the same.)  The *only* case where your dangly might make a diffference 
in getting someone on the poll is if a particular set of royalty decides to
give more weight to recommendations from within the order.  But once someone
is on the poll, all Crescents are pretty much equal, and the person will only
get the award (in the general case...) if *most* of the order is convinced.
I haven't been to an order meeting yet, so my votes have come entirely from
personal knowledge and conversations with other Crescents.  (You should plan
on your phone bill going up a bit....)

Actually, your hardest task will probably be this: when So-And-So's name does
come up on the poll, you should work very hard to make sure you don't downgrade
your vote just because the person has obnoxious friends.

Don't crawl under a table and hide; just tell these people to write the person
in themselves.  If you're feeling particularly assertive, you might mention
how rude this behavior of theirs is, too.

Good luck to you!


