Re:  Same sex consorts.  How quickly we degenerate into "discussing
the arguements" instead of discussing the topic.  I finally figured
out why I don't like the idea of same sex consorts:

ITS BAD THEATER!   ITS BAD THEATER!

i.e. Court is basically ad lib theatre done to entertain the masses
(and maybe actually get some useful things done at the same time).

So, is the idea, with regard to same sex consorts, that one person
"look male" and the other "look female"?  i.e. if my "persona" is
female I should "count" as a female with regard to being a consort?

Or is the idea that a fighter should be able to fight/reign for/with
anyone they please, regardless of sex?

** On a somewhat side subject to this **

As all entrants to a Crown/Principality List (and their consorts)
must be acceptable to the King/Prince, and the King/Prince may
restrict the entrants.  Go ahead and allow same sex consorts (by
mundane definition), but restrict the entrants that would be "BAD
THEATER".

i.e. if the reigning King/Prince thinks that the "same sex couple",
would (if they won) use the Throne in a manner unacceptable, then
they shouldn't be allowed to enter.  By the way, this is an
available option for other situations also.

Re:  Personas, et al.

Out here in the West, personas aren't as big a deal as in other
kingdoms (at least from what I can tell).  From experience, many
people in the West don't have personas.  They may have a "persona",
but the don't have a "Persona".

i.e. they are interested in one region/time more than another, so
they create a persona, however, they don't limit themselves in any
way based on this persona, or change their behavior.

Also, are not awards/devices/etc all registered to "your mundane,
legal entity"?  i.e. I don't care if you change your "Persona",
you're still a KSCA (or whatever).  There is no requirement that
someone ever have a persona.  Example:  Sir William the Lucky
doesn't have a persona.

If we start basing all our rules/laws/ideas/reactions, based purely
on "Personas", I change mine week to week, based on what I want to
do.  (i.e. lets be a barbarian this week so I can hassle people, and
get sick in their pavilions.  but next week lets be all courtly and
pomp and circumstance.  etc.)

More later,

