Subject: mail making bibliography


The article I mentioned a few weeks ago about metallurgy and mail is
Cyril Stanley Smith, 1959. "Methods of Making Chain Mail (14th to 18th 
Centuries): A Metallographic Note".  Technology and Culture I #1 1959.

The best SCA publication I've seen on mail making is 
"The Art of Mail Making" by Sir Polidor Haraldsson (mundanely, Brian Flax).
The copy I have is not dated, but is at least six years old, so may be gone
out of print or been revised.

The Compleat Anachronist has some information on mail-making in 
"Selection from the Hammer, Part I", Compleat Anachronist 2 (September 1982).


E. Martin Burgess did some careful studies of specific mail pieces in the 
late 50's and early 60's.  I particularly like his articles:

Wlliam Reid and E. Martin Burgess "A Habergeon of Westwale" Antiquaries Journal
Volume XL Jan-April 1960

E Martin Burgess. "The mail-maker's technique"  Antiquaries Journal
XXXVIII 1953 (48--55)

E Martin Burgess. "Further Research into theConstruction of Mail Garments"
Antiquaries Journal 1953. (193--202)

E. Martin Burgess "14th Century mail hood in the Royal Scottish Museum, 
Edinburgh"  Journal of the Arms and Armor Society v2 p.59.

The mail hood looks like a particularly good project for riveted mail as it is
small, and complete details of its construction are given in the article.

