intendend, not merely as rulers, but as symbols and archetypes: the fighter of 
chivalry, puissance, and other knightly/kingly virtues, and the consort of 
courtesy, and skill at gentle arts.  In western european culture, esp. western 
european medieval culture (which is what we're trying to recreate), a ruling 
pair is male/female.  (the warriors of classical greece were sometimes 
inspired by male lovers, see also alexander the great, if you want to start a 
