Landed counts?  Well, why not?  I've been musing onthis subject for a while now
as I work on my maps.  I've noticed osme things about the way we do business in
the SCA and I'm going to share my thoughts with the rest of you.

We have only two kinds of landed nobility in the SCA:barons and royalty.
Barons are Appointed Forever, kings, queens, and princes serve only six months.
If you get an "inadequate" monarch, the damage he can do is limited byhis short
reign. An inadequate baron is forever.  I have never heard of a baron being
deprived of his ofice, though I suppose a king could do that if he felt it
necessary.  The only way a baron is normally removed is for him to resign.

  And
some of the barons, while being perfectly nice people, don't really fulfill
their duties as baron.  They've been baron forever, the novelty has worn off,
they're no longer active,  once in a while they show up at events, ask for
reccommendations, and then hand out a bunch of baronial service awards to
people they've never even met.  I don't know if there is a rule requiring
barons to bve members in good standing, but if there isn't, there should be.
If a baron can't even get it togehter enough to send in his subscription then
the people could get a new baron who would take an active leadership role in
the group.  A baron ought to attend all events in his barony, show up regularly
for meetings, fighter practice, guild meetings, and whateveer other activities
his barony sponsors.  If he can't do this on a regular basis, he shouldn't be
baron, and his resignation is in order.

I personally favor putting a time limit, say two years, on a landed baron. If
he's been a great baron, the Crown can reappoint him.  If not, the Crown can
pick somebody who's going to be more active.  Or maybe the members of the
group ought ought pick their own baron, they have to live with him after all.
Baronial Tourney?  Nah, stickjocks have too much influence already.  Barons
ought to be well rounded and knowledgeable about all aspects of the SCA... An
arts pentathalon perhaps?  And if groups wante dto join together into a larger
alliance, they could form countied or cushies with someone of their choosing at
the head.  That person would then have to be confirmed in his rank and holdings
by the monarch.  That is how it was done in period.  

Of course, the monarchs would have to have  the right to make peers of that
rank.  After all monarchs in period bestowed rank and titles upon people they
felt were deserving of them.  Thus we would ahve a landed nobility chosen by
the people and confirmed by the king, and a court nobility, chosen by the
monarch.  Landed nobles would outrank court nobles with the same title.  

Then what about ex-royalty?  At the moment, it is customary to make them
vicounts, counts, and dukes.  But why?  The king, as the bearer of the Crown,
is preeminet in all the land.  But it is the Crown which is the source an
dsymbol of the Dream, of all honor, courtesy, and valor.   The king is only a
fallible human who for the moment happens to be the guardian of the Crown.  We
all can think of people who we thought were not really good monarchs, and yet
these people are autmatically rewarded with the highest titles the SCA has to
offer.   I think about Duke Sir Obnoxious the Violent and I shudder that this
man has one of the highest awardds we can bestow.  And he got the award simply
because he's a darn good stick jock.

Even the obnoxious people who have served as monarchs deserve recognition
because they did put a lot of time and effort into it, and they did do some
things right, and anyhow, only the people who have sat in the hot seat really
know what it's about.  Yes, there ought to be a reward for ex-royalty,a nd an
obligation that they offer up the wisdom of their experience to the current
monarchs or peers.  In the Midrealm there is the Order of the Rose into which
exqueens are automatically inducted.  I don't know too much about it, but the
purpose seems to be to recognize and reward courtesy and chivalry.  That's the
sort of thing ex-royalty are good for.   They've met an awful lot of people,
read a lot of letters, been to a lot of places, royalty have a greater
familiarlity with what goes on throughout the kingdom than most of the rest of
us do.

This is a drastic reordering of the way the SCA does business, but it is both
more medeival, and more workable than the current system.

And while I'm spouting heresy, can we please choose our royalty some other way
than the through the Stickjocks' Delight?  If we choose our kings with a
tourney, we  get kings who are good at bashing people on the head, which is not
a useful skill for the smooth and diplomatic running of the kingdom.  A kingdom
wide tourney to choose the King's Champion is a perfectly reasonable thing,
a kingdom wide tourney to choose a Lord General of the Armies or a Warlord is
also reasoanble, they are martial offices and martial prowess is necessary to
to them.  But the king is supposed to be the patron of the arts  and
sciences, service and the traditions of the kingdom, and the military arts are 
 just part  of the arts he should be knowledgeable about.

Yours in service to a reorganized SCA,
