From: "]ke Eldberg" <CONS.ELF@AIDA.CSD.UU.SE>
Subject: Face thrusting
Message-ID: <890328025602.10.CONS.ELF@AIDA.CSD.UU.SE>
 
If my information is correct, there is a theory about SCA combat which states
that we are wearing chainmail and open-faced helmets, i.e. 11th century Norman
armor. This has been taken as a reason to allow face thrusts.
 
Face thrusts don't need to have the force of a killing blow. It's enough to
poke somebody in the face to get a kill. The theory is that a sword thrust
in your face would produce such pain and bleeding (which would blind you)
that even if the thrust itself did not kill you, you could no longer defend
yourself and would thus be killed by the next blow.
 
I disapprove of face thrusting. 
 
It can certainly be argued that the above explanation is authentic. But SCA
combat is not authentic. In a life-and-death combat, knights would hack at
their enemie's feet, they would kick them in the groin or knock them down
with their bodies, or trip them, and use all kinds of tricks and lethal
violence which SCA combat never uses. We cannot simulate these things for
reasons of safety, even in wars.
 
Single combat in the SCA is supposed to be chivalrous, not intending to really
kill but only to defeat an opponent by making a "good blow". Medieval tourna-
ments were not intended to kill people. Often, thrusting was banned as too
dangerous (at least, this is what I've heard, correct me if I'm wrong).
 
Face thrusting definitely belongs in the realm of lethal violence which could
never be simulated without serious damage if we were using open-faced helms 
and real swords. Thus, it would have to be banned from a tournament if the
object was not to kill. 
 
If we allow face thrusting, we should also allow all those other modes of
violence which were available even in peaceful tournaments, such as throwing 
your bodyweight against your opponent to bring him down. Face thrusting is
simply *too efficient* if it is combined with all the other restraints that
we have in SCA combat.
 
At least, that is how I feel. I want to be killed by a Good Blow, not by a
light prod on my faceplate.
 
