    defense against it are something to try to develop.  

    (As an aside, what do Eastrealmers think of the new face-thrusting
    rules for Crown Tourney?)

For what it's worth, one fighter's opinions about thrusting.  I don't do it -
not because I think it's not chivalrous (the people who thrust at my stomach
invariably find my cup...), not because I think it isn't period (broadswords
were used to smash and hack, not stab), but because it is a gimmic.  I try to
concentrate on simple, direct attacks, and simple, tight defense.  If you can't
master "the basics" then the more complicated moves will forever escape you. I
am too busy blocking my opponents blows and throwing my own, to look for "that
special opening" which would allow a good thrust.  Thus, I don't even put
thrusting tips on my swords.

His Royal Highness Morguhn has specifically BANNED face thrusting from Spring
Crownt Tourney, which is, by the way, in Lakewood, New Jersey (the Barony of
Carillion) on May 13th.

