   > And now, a question of my own.  How do you lay the padding inside a
> helm.  I assume it must be done after welding, but is there a method
> to it other than simply covering it with glue and shoving it in
> the bottom?

   Best solution I've seen that avoids glue or double-sided tape is one used
by John the Artificer, from our area.  He put together a flight-cap style hat
(aka "Snoopy and The Red Court Baron" style) with the padding attached
to _it_, in pads and tubes.  He puts this on, then puts on the helmet over it.
The helmet proper has _no_ padding in it, just a chin strap.  This way he
can remove the padding, wash it (oh my, to be able to do that with mine!),
modify it, etc., without tearing things out of the helm.  Makes banging dings
out of ones hat easier, too, I would suppose.

