    Subject: Service Awards and Behaviour
    I have a question for the folk of the Rialto.
    If someone in your group has performed a LOT of service...
    What do you do when this person has, over the past years, aroused
    so much hostility in the group...
    This is someone who doesn't conform to the conservative behaviour
    of the group...
    This person's service has been real and valuable....
    The Fret is in the gift of the Crown, of course, yet I realize my
    recommendation would carry some weight.... What do I do?

You have a doozy of a problem there, as those who have already
commented on this matter have noted.  I somewhat agree with Hal Ravn,
who suggested various ways of working with this unfortunate to better
his/her behavior and bring it up to a gentle standard.  But it sounds
like you and those around you are doing or have done this to the
extent that all involved can stand.  If that is the case, perhaps the
following would suit your conscience:
    Write to the Crown.  State all the facts you know, both this
person's extensive service and his or her bad personal behavior.  Give
your argument, or if you will, your ruminations on WHETHER this person
deserves the Purple Fret, based on the facts you have noted.  Include
your ambivalence concerning the situation.
    Then send it off, and let the Crown worry about it; you will have
done your duty by explaining the situation, and by giving all the pros
and cons you know of.  The most important thing is to alert the Crown
that here exists someone who -may- deserve the award; the Crowns of
the East are eternally complaining that they don't know about all the
Eastern folk who deserve awards, which given the size of the East is
undoubtedly true.
    Certainly, if you can stand to give this person further aid and
encouragement to improve his or her behavior, and if s/he can stand to
accept the same, do so.  But don't kill yourself about it; this person
appears to be adult, and so is responsible for his/her own behavior,
however gentle or un-.  Good luck..

