scrolls this gentleman has done, he hasn't charged for one. I believe
he even does scrolls by request without charging for them (as opposed
to making an award scroll at the request of the crown or in
the service of the college of scribes.) He only charges for exotic
materials (such as gold-leaf) and then only if he doesn't have any 
on hand.  His reasoning is that every award scroll is in service to
the kingdom and shouldn't be charged for. I think scroll-making in
this context is fundamentally different than say armor-making and
even fundamentally different than making scrolls on commision which
