     In an effort to save bleary eyes, this letter concerns only 'New
and Different,' to quote our senechal.

     Chivalry:  If it were possible to catalog the set of behaviours
which constitute chivalry, everyone in the society would be able to be
flawlessly chivalrous.  However, chivalry is highly SITUATIONAL as well
as personal.  At each event in a person's life requiring a judgement
call, it can be difficult to stop, consider, and THEN act.  To consider,
and then choose the chivalrous course, is that much harder, as it is rarely
the same choice as a gut reaction.  I consider it a challenge to which
I am always attempting to rise.  A society-specific case: being the voice
of reason and being willing to believe the best of others.  Heaven knows
most of us have a 'gossip-tooth' like a candy-lover has a 'sweet-tooth.'

