mentioned.  To quote an article from the Known World Handbook, the great
joy of the society, to me, is being 'a Creator, not a Consumer.'  The mundane
world we live in is extremely consumer-oriented.  I am often left to wonder
where is the personal satisfaction in the lives of my mundane co-workers
who are either shopping or watching television.  Ouch!  I have dabbled
happily in inkle-weaving, wool- and flax-spinning, mead and applejack
brewing, cooking, garb-making, armor-making, and very soon heavy list.
I never go anywhere without a drop spindle, nor would many women before
(approx.) 1300.  The point is not the yarn I spin, but the sheer joy of
watching the spindle go 'round.  The satisfaction comes in the DOING, not
the HAVING, n'est-ce pas?

