Subject: Boring chainmail

An anecdotal suggestion, for relieving the boredom of chainmail manufacture...

One friend of mine, several years back, was making a chainmail hauberk for
another friend. As anyone who makes chain knows, this is a pretty big project,
especially as one's first. Well, she found that the best way to get the job
along was to take the equipment along to all the parties and post-revels she
went to, and take clear joy in the manufacture. Inevitably, someone would
say, "Wow, that's neat; how do you make that?". She would show them, and
ask if they would like to try it. This would lead to more inquiries, and, by
the end of the evening, she would have *lots* of fresh links. Those of us
who hung out with her started calling the hauberk "The Carolingian White
Fence". (Think Twain).

